WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.833 --> 00:00:10.333
[rain pattering]

2
00:00:15.792 --> 00:00:17.292
[thunder crashes]

3
00:00:18.708 --> 00:00:20.583
[suspenseful music playing]

4
00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:28.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

5
00:00:31.167 --> 00:00:32.458
[thunder rumbling]

6
00:00:40.125 --> 00:00:42.083
[suspenseful music continues]

7
00:00:56.250 --> 00:00:57.458
[Gertrude] Hayden?

8
00:01:02.250 --> 00:01:03.417
Who's this?

9
00:01:06.167 --> 00:01:07.708
He's my son.

10
00:01:10.750 --> 00:01:11.958
He's a Payne.

11
00:01:14.792 --> 00:01:16.250
What have you done?

12
00:01:19.500 --> 00:01:21.958
[dramatic music playing]

13
00:01:33.292 --> 00:01:34.542
[grunting]

14
00:01:34.625 --> 00:01:36.000
[tap water running]

15
00:01:53.333 --> 00:01:54.542
Hey. buddy. what are you doing?

16
00:01:55.458 --> 00:01:56.625
Dad!

17
00:01:57.250 --> 00:01:58.500
Hey. Come on.

18
00:01:58.583 --> 00:02:00.083
Oh!

19
00:02:02.083 --> 00:02:05.917
Do you want to watch me play Fortnite?
I've got this cool new Star Wars skin.

20
00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:08.250
Well. I would. but. um…

21
00:02:09.125 --> 00:02:10.958
I got a surprise for you.

22
00:02:11.042 --> 00:02:13.792
We're gonna take a trip.
You. me. and your grandmother.

23
00:02:13.875 --> 00:02:14.708
Where?

24
00:02:14.792 --> 00:02:17.708
If I told you. it wouldn't be a surprise.
would it?

25
00:02:18.208 --> 00:02:19.667
But I need you to pack. okay?

26
00:02:19.750 --> 00:02:21.125
Only what you really want to take.

27
00:02:21.208 --> 00:02:23.708
and anything else you need.
we'll buy when we get there.

28
00:02:23.792 --> 00:02:24.708
Wait.

29
00:02:25.833 --> 00:02:27.292
Are we moving again?

30
00:02:28.917 --> 00:02:29.833
We are.

31
00:02:30.333 --> 00:02:31.833
Are we ever coming back?

32
00:02:31.917 --> 00:02:33.375
[chuckles softly]

33
00:02:33.458 --> 00:02:35.167
Go ahead and start packing.

34
00:02:36.125 --> 00:02:37.542
[Rachel] David is innocent!

35
00:02:37.625 --> 00:02:41.375
His son is alive. and he's being held
by a man named Hayden Payne!

36
00:02:41.458 --> 00:02:44.417
-No. Hayden Payne has been helping you.
-No. he hasn't.

37
00:02:44.500 --> 00:02:47.417
He's been manipulating us
to keep us from the truth.

38
00:02:47.500 --> 00:02:48.958
He's about to leave town.

39
00:02:49.042 --> 00:02:51.542
He left me this cryptic voicemail earlier
saying goodbye.

40
00:02:51.625 --> 00:02:53.208
-Wait. he's gonna run?
-Yeah.

41
00:02:53.292 --> 00:02:57.375
And if he does. if he does.
we will never see Matthew again!

42
00:02:58.458 --> 00:03:00.625
I know how crazy this all sounds.

43
00:03:03.250 --> 00:03:05.875
That boy I found that night.
it's not Matthew.

44
00:03:07.833 --> 00:03:09.167
I know.

45
00:03:11.167 --> 00:03:12.833
I know it wasn't Matthew.

46
00:03:15.833 --> 00:03:17.667
It's a little boy named Martin Bischoff.

47
00:03:17.750 --> 00:03:20.708
He disappeared from a Swiss orphanage
owned by the Paynes.

48
00:03:20.792 --> 00:03:22.375
[tense music playing]

49
00:03:31.875 --> 00:03:34.708
I took care of the detective.
and I cleaned up the scene.

50
00:03:35.583 --> 00:03:38.750
But it is only a matter of time
before the FBI come calling.

51
00:03:39.667 --> 00:03:40.792
We have to leave.

52
00:03:40.875 --> 00:03:43.500
This is not gonna end
just because you're on a beach somewhere.

53
00:03:43.583 --> 00:03:45.375
They're gonna reopen the case.

54
00:03:46.083 --> 00:03:49.792
and then you and Hayden will spend
the rest of your life on the run.

55
00:03:49.875 --> 00:03:51.792
What other choice do we have?

56
00:03:51.875 --> 00:03:55.167
People think Matthew Burroughs
might still be alive.

57
00:03:57.292 --> 00:03:58.542
What if he wasn't?

58
00:03:59.500 --> 00:04:00.500
What are you saying?

59
00:04:00.583 --> 00:04:04.792
I'm saying what if he died that night.
and his body was never found?

60
00:04:04.875 --> 00:04:06.667
Nothing to connect to you.

61
00:04:06.750 --> 00:04:08.083
No need to run.

62
00:04:09.792 --> 00:04:12.500
As far as the world is concerned.

63
00:04:12.583 --> 00:04:14.167
he is a Payne.

64
00:04:15.833 --> 00:04:18.292
He may be the last of the Paynes.

65
00:04:18.375 --> 00:04:20.250
and Hayden loves him.

66
00:04:21.667 --> 00:04:22.958
Am I clear?

67
00:04:23.042 --> 00:04:24.917
[dour music playing]

68
00:04:34.792 --> 00:04:37.167
-What were you two talking about?
-How's Theo?

69
00:04:38.292 --> 00:04:39.250
He's good.

70
00:04:39.792 --> 00:04:41.208
He's in his room packing.

71
00:04:41.792 --> 00:04:44.000
-Did he see anything?
-No.

72
00:04:44.583 --> 00:04:47.000
Make sure he stays in his room
until we leave.

73
00:04:48.458 --> 00:04:49.375
Hayden.

74
00:04:54.458 --> 00:04:56.333
That detective knew everything.

75
00:04:57.000 --> 00:05:00.917
You did what you had to.
and what you needed to for your son.

76
00:05:05.000 --> 00:05:06.000
Yeah.

77
00:05:07.875 --> 00:05:09.833
Wait. if you knew the body wasn't Matthew.

78
00:05:09.917 --> 00:05:12.458
why aren't the FBI out
looking for my son right now?

79
00:05:12.542 --> 00:05:13.542
It's not that simple.

80
00:05:13.625 --> 00:05:17.375
What do you mean it's not that simple?
He's been kidnapped by a psychopath!

81
00:05:17.458 --> 00:05:20.292
I've been suspended. so without
any hard evidence. I'm on my own.

82
00:05:20.375 --> 00:05:22.500
Well. fine. there are
a dozen cops out there right now.

83
00:05:22.583 --> 00:05:24.333
-I'll just go and ask one of them.
-You can't do that.

84
00:05:24.417 --> 00:05:26.542
-Why not?
-'Cause you said it. he's a psychopath.

85
00:05:26.625 --> 00:05:28.667
So if he's surrounded
by cops and he feels threatened.

86
00:05:28.750 --> 00:05:30.667
then who knows
what he might do to Matthew?

87
00:05:30.750 --> 00:05:32.917
The Payne estate is a half hour
outside the city.

88
00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:34.958
Even if we leave now.
we may not catch them.

89
00:05:35.042 --> 00:05:37.125
Okay. we gotta delay him.
We gotta get there before he leaves.

90
00:05:37.208 --> 00:05:38.625
How? How will we do that?

91
00:05:39.917 --> 00:05:41.250
After I was attacked.

92
00:05:42.125 --> 00:05:44.292
he tried to convince me
to leave the country with him.

93
00:05:44.375 --> 00:05:46.167
He's not gonna think
that you changed your mind.

94
00:05:46.250 --> 00:05:47.375
He will…

95
00:05:48.667 --> 00:05:50.667
if he thinks you've been arrested.

96
00:05:50.750 --> 00:05:52.542
[dramatic music playing]

97
00:05:55.417 --> 00:05:57.458
Rachel. I'm glad you called.

98
00:05:58.083 --> 00:06:00.542
Didn't think I'd ever hear from you again.

99
00:06:01.167 --> 00:06:02.583
Sorry. what?

100
00:06:03.833 --> 00:06:06.500
Uh. yeah. Yeah. okay.

101
00:06:07.292 --> 00:06:08.417
I could do that.

102
00:06:10.125 --> 00:06:12.375
You think Ronald will care
that I'm stealing his car?

103
00:06:12.458 --> 00:06:14.792
I don't even know where he is right now.

104
00:06:15.708 --> 00:06:18.542
Oh. uh. about that. Ronald.
I actually had him arrested.

105
00:06:18.625 --> 00:06:19.500
What?

106
00:06:19.583 --> 00:06:21.333
I'll clear it up. don't worry.

107
00:06:22.333 --> 00:06:25.083
-[David] Be right behind you. Be careful.
-I need you to put these on.

108
00:06:25.167 --> 00:06:27.208
If anybody stops us.
I've arrested you. got it?

109
00:06:29.750 --> 00:06:30.958
-David?
-[David] Yeah?

110
00:06:33.625 --> 00:06:35.792
There's so much
I-I need to say to you. but…

111
00:06:37.625 --> 00:06:39.042
Yeah. you don't have to.

112
00:06:40.625 --> 00:06:42.083
It's the past.

113
00:06:43.250 --> 00:06:45.125
Bring our son home. okay?

114
00:06:45.875 --> 00:06:47.417
Whatever it takes.

115
00:06:47.917 --> 00:06:49.167
You bring him home.

116
00:06:49.250 --> 00:06:51.375
[dramatic music playing]

117
00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:59.708
And in breaking news.
The Boston Globeis now reporting

118
00:06:59.792 --> 00:07:04.458
that escaped fugitive David Burroughs
has been apprehended by the Boston police.

119
00:07:04.542 --> 00:07:06.083
Holy shit. they caught him.

120
00:07:06.167 --> 00:07:08.500
-It doesn't mean anything.
-He's going back to prison.

121
00:07:08.583 --> 00:07:09.792
For how long?

122
00:07:10.750 --> 00:07:13.250
He will be exonerated eventually.

123
00:07:13.333 --> 00:07:15.750
and then he'll start
looking all over again.

124
00:07:15.833 --> 00:07:17.667
Only this time. as a free man.

125
00:07:19.208 --> 00:07:20.458
We have to leave.

126
00:07:20.542 --> 00:07:22.000
[cell phone vibrating]

127
00:07:24.792 --> 00:07:25.792
Rachel.

128
00:07:27.167 --> 00:07:28.000
Are you okay?

129
00:07:29.083 --> 00:07:31.708
-[Rachel] David's been arrested.
-I saw on the news. What happened?

130
00:07:31.792 --> 00:07:35.583
We broke into the hospital to find Heller.
and David was caught.

131
00:07:35.667 --> 00:07:38.083
I got away. but I have nowhere to go.

132
00:07:38.167 --> 00:07:39.708
I don't know what to do.

133
00:07:40.417 --> 00:07:43.792
Hayden. the worst part is Heller's gone.
and we have no way to find Matthew now.

134
00:07:44.375 --> 00:07:45.250
How can I help?

135
00:07:46.375 --> 00:07:48.583
You told me we could
leave together. right?

136
00:07:48.667 --> 00:07:50.500
If the offer still stands.

137
00:07:50.583 --> 00:07:52.042
I'm ready. Hayden.

138
00:07:52.542 --> 00:07:55.167
I'm at my mother's estate.
How quick can you get here?

139
00:07:55.750 --> 00:07:58.208
I was hoping you'd say that.
'cause I'm almost there.

140
00:07:58.792 --> 00:08:00.333
-See you soon.
-Okay.

141
00:08:02.417 --> 00:08:04.792
How stupid can you be?

142
00:08:04.875 --> 00:08:07.042
I don't understand
your obsession with this woman.

143
00:08:07.125 --> 00:08:08.292
I love her. Mother.

144
00:08:08.375 --> 00:08:12.333
Oh. darling boy. there's a difference
between love and obsession.

145
00:08:12.417 --> 00:08:14.208
She is going to be your downfall.

146
00:08:14.292 --> 00:08:16.542
Is that why you had Stephano
try and kill her?

147
00:08:17.292 --> 00:08:21.125
Someone has to make the hard choices.
and it's certainly not going to be you.

148
00:08:21.792 --> 00:08:23.042
If anybody goes near us--

149
00:08:27.333 --> 00:08:29.458
There is no happily ever after
on this one.

150
00:08:30.042 --> 00:08:33.125
You don't think
that she'll know her own nephew?

151
00:08:33.792 --> 00:08:36.875
This whole thing started
because she saw that photograph

152
00:08:36.958 --> 00:08:38.542
and knew it was Matthew Burroughs.

153
00:08:38.625 --> 00:08:40.417
[Theo] Who's Matthew Burroughs?

154
00:08:41.625 --> 00:08:42.542
Theo.

155
00:08:44.917 --> 00:08:47.042
You know you're not supposed to eavesdrop.

156
00:08:47.125 --> 00:08:49.333
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to.

157
00:08:49.417 --> 00:08:52.875
It's okay. buddy. Your grandmother and I
were just talking about our trip.

158
00:08:52.958 --> 00:08:56.042
And I can't find Rhino.
and I want to take him with us.

159
00:08:56.625 --> 00:08:59.625
Oh. okay. Well. I'll tell you what.

160
00:09:00.333 --> 00:09:03.125
Go back upstairs.
and I'll be right up there to help you.

161
00:09:03.208 --> 00:09:05.042
[gentle music playing]

162
00:09:12.667 --> 00:09:14.125
When she arrives.

163
00:09:15.208 --> 00:09:17.292
tell her that you can't help her.

164
00:09:18.042 --> 00:09:20.625
And then you get her to leave.

165
00:09:34.125 --> 00:09:36.000
[ominous music playing]

166
00:09:53.333 --> 00:09:54.958
[crying softly]

167
00:10:02.875 --> 00:10:04.125
It's just a precaution.

168
00:10:04.750 --> 00:10:05.833
Smart.

169
00:10:05.917 --> 00:10:08.375
Yeah. Whoever's behind all this
knows that I've been helping you.

170
00:10:10.000 --> 00:10:11.958
Thank you for letting me come here.

171
00:10:12.042 --> 00:10:13.833
I didn't know where else to go.

172
00:10:13.917 --> 00:10:15.042
Yeah.

173
00:10:18.500 --> 00:10:19.375
What?

174
00:10:20.167 --> 00:10:22.750
I can't help you anymore. Rachel.

175
00:10:22.833 --> 00:10:24.708
I thought you wanted to leave together.

176
00:10:24.792 --> 00:10:26.000
I do.

177
00:10:26.583 --> 00:10:28.833
Then what's the problem?

178
00:10:33.000 --> 00:10:34.417
Your mother. of course.

179
00:10:36.250 --> 00:10:39.417
I'm just confused because I thought
you said you wanted to protect me.

180
00:10:40.167 --> 00:10:41.500
[sighs]

181
00:10:42.500 --> 00:10:43.958
And I need you.

182
00:10:45.083 --> 00:10:46.833
Right now more than ever.

183
00:10:49.625 --> 00:10:52.167
You know the only time
I've ever felt really safe is with you.

184
00:10:53.250 --> 00:10:54.542
If we leave. we…

185
00:10:55.417 --> 00:10:56.708
we can't come back.

186
00:10:58.208 --> 00:11:00.125
There's nothing for me here.

187
00:11:00.208 --> 00:11:02.042
Hasn't been for a long time.

188
00:11:06.375 --> 00:11:08.333
I want a fresh start together.

189
00:11:11.167 --> 00:11:12.625
Do you want that?

190
00:11:21.000 --> 00:11:24.042
Just. uh. wait in the great room.

191
00:11:24.125 --> 00:11:24.958
Okay.

192
00:11:25.042 --> 00:11:27.000
I'm gonna use the ladies' room
before we go.

193
00:11:27.083 --> 00:11:28.875
-It's down the hall. You know where it is.
-Yeah.

194
00:11:28.958 --> 00:11:30.958
[dramatic music playing]

195
00:11:41.583 --> 00:11:42.958
Thank you for helping me.

196
00:11:43.042 --> 00:11:46.375
Don't thank me.
I'm taking you in as soon as this is over.

197
00:11:46.458 --> 00:11:48.375
This is just a pit stop.
as far as I'm concerned.

198
00:11:48.458 --> 00:11:50.583
As long as I get Matthew back.
that's all that matters.

199
00:11:51.458 --> 00:11:53.083
[cell phone ringing]

200
00:11:58.917 --> 00:12:00.000
It's my partner.

201
00:12:00.083 --> 00:12:03.042
And I'm guessing
he wouldn't approve of our pit stop.

202
00:12:04.208 --> 00:12:05.375
He would not.

203
00:12:06.625 --> 00:12:09.042
[Greer's voice]You've reached
Agent Sarah Greer. I'm not able to…

204
00:12:09.125 --> 00:12:12.250
Oh. damn it. Sarah.
will you answer the damn phone?

205
00:12:12.333 --> 00:12:14.542
[exhales in frustration] That's it.

206
00:12:14.625 --> 00:12:15.917
I'm getting out of here.

207
00:12:16.000 --> 00:12:17.083
[monitors beeping]

208
00:12:17.167 --> 00:12:18.625
Ah! Ah!

209
00:12:18.708 --> 00:12:19.833
[groaning]

210
00:12:23.083 --> 00:12:24.375
[beeping stops]

211
00:12:24.458 --> 00:12:27.750
Hey. this is gonna sound crazy.
Um. my name's Cheryl.

212
00:12:27.833 --> 00:12:31.583
-I know who you are. Dr. Dreason.
-Your partner. Agent Greer. She just left.

213
00:12:31.667 --> 00:12:32.750
Left to go where?

214
00:12:32.833 --> 00:12:34.875
To find my son. And. uh…

215
00:12:36.500 --> 00:12:37.542
David's with her.

216
00:12:37.625 --> 00:12:39.333
So he wasn't arrested.

217
00:12:39.417 --> 00:12:41.167
-No.
-You know where they're headed?

218
00:12:41.250 --> 00:12:42.125
The Payne estate.

219
00:12:42.208 --> 00:12:45.083
Hayden Payne was behind everything
that happened that night.

220
00:12:45.167 --> 00:12:48.583
Now. she said the FBI
couldn't do anything without proof.

221
00:12:49.833 --> 00:12:50.667
I have proof.

222
00:12:51.417 --> 00:12:54.208
Philip Mackenzie ran a DNA test for me.

223
00:12:54.792 --> 00:12:57.875
That proves the blood found
that night wasn't Matthew's.

224
00:12:57.958 --> 00:13:01.625
Which means the DNA results
used at the trial were doctored.

225
00:13:02.625 --> 00:13:03.958
David's innocent.

226
00:13:04.583 --> 00:13:07.083
My son is alive. Please.

227
00:13:07.958 --> 00:13:09.500
I need your help.

228
00:13:09.583 --> 00:13:11.583
[dramatic music playing]

229
00:13:14.500 --> 00:13:15.500
[tap water runs]

230
00:13:19.250 --> 00:13:20.917
[cell phone snaps closed]

231
00:13:22.167 --> 00:13:23.500
[turns tap water off]

232
00:13:29.917 --> 00:13:31.583
-I thought I made myself clear.
-You did.

233
00:13:31.667 --> 00:13:34.375
-Then why is she still here?
-I can make this work.

234
00:13:34.458 --> 00:13:36.958
Hayden. she doesn't love you.

235
00:13:38.125 --> 00:13:39.500
We have a problem.

236
00:13:39.583 --> 00:13:40.875
No kidding.

237
00:13:40.958 --> 00:13:42.917
David Burroughs was never arrested.

238
00:13:43.000 --> 00:13:43.917
What?

239
00:13:44.000 --> 00:13:47.083
He's not in BPD or FBI custody.

240
00:13:47.167 --> 00:13:51.167
No one knows whyThe Globeran that story
or who the source was.

241
00:13:55.292 --> 00:13:56.125
Rachel.

242
00:13:56.208 --> 00:13:58.208
You still think you can make this work?

243
00:13:58.292 --> 00:14:00.583
Burroughs is probably on his way here.

244
00:14:01.292 --> 00:14:02.625
What do you want to do?

245
00:14:05.292 --> 00:14:06.333
Let him come.

246
00:14:07.958 --> 00:14:09.333
She did us a favor.

247
00:14:09.917 --> 00:14:13.833
No one will question the killing
of two dangerous fugitives

248
00:14:13.917 --> 00:14:16.042
who've trespassed on private property.

249
00:14:16.125 --> 00:14:18.167
And I assume you finally agree.

250
00:14:20.458 --> 00:14:22.458
[foreboding music playing]

251
00:14:31.833 --> 00:14:33.708
[foreboding music continues]

252
00:14:54.417 --> 00:14:55.333
Get back in the car.

253
00:14:55.417 --> 00:14:56.583
I'm coming with you.

254
00:14:57.833 --> 00:15:00.042
You're still a fugitive. all right?
I said I'd help you.

255
00:15:00.125 --> 00:15:02.208
-We're not teaming up.
-You're right. we're not.

256
00:15:03.667 --> 00:15:05.292
I came out here on my own.
You followed me.

257
00:15:05.375 --> 00:15:08.417
And then when I get my son back.
you can arrest me and take me to jail.

258
00:15:08.500 --> 00:15:09.833
[cell phone vibrating]

259
00:15:12.875 --> 00:15:13.875
[Greer] It's Rachel.

260
00:15:14.625 --> 00:15:16.542
There's armed guards at the house.

261
00:15:19.667 --> 00:15:22.750
I can help you. Now just let me--
Let me find him. please.

262
00:15:31.750 --> 00:15:34.750
-You okay?
-Yeah. just a little overwhelmed.

263
00:15:36.208 --> 00:15:37.333
You're safe now.

264
00:15:37.417 --> 00:15:40.958
And the fact that you're here
tells me you finally want what I want.

265
00:15:43.000 --> 00:15:43.833
I do.

266
00:15:44.500 --> 00:15:45.792
-You do?
-I do.

267
00:15:56.417 --> 00:15:58.083
Whoa. what are you doing?

268
00:15:59.083 --> 00:16:00.125
Hayden.

269
00:16:04.375 --> 00:16:05.208
Hayden?

270
00:16:06.500 --> 00:16:10.417
-Please. let me explain.
-I would've done anything for you.

271
00:16:10.500 --> 00:16:13.083
Please. please. just listen to me.

272
00:16:13.667 --> 00:16:14.917
You lied to me.

273
00:16:21.667 --> 00:16:23.500
You broke my heart.

274
00:16:36.500 --> 00:16:37.583
How do we get in?

275
00:16:37.667 --> 00:16:38.667
Side entrance.

276
00:16:38.750 --> 00:16:39.917
I can cover you.

277
00:16:40.000 --> 00:16:41.375
[gunshots]

278
00:16:43.917 --> 00:16:45.458
[vibrating]

279
00:16:46.042 --> 00:16:49.042
I hope you've come to your senses
and decided to tell me where she is.

280
00:16:49.125 --> 00:16:50.042
Sure. Julie.

281
00:16:50.625 --> 00:16:53.417
She's on her way to the Payne estate
to arrest Hayden Payne

282
00:16:53.500 --> 00:16:54.875
for murder and kidnapping.

283
00:16:54.958 --> 00:16:55.958
She's suspended.

284
00:16:56.042 --> 00:16:58.667
She can't arrest anyone.
You need to stop her.

285
00:16:58.750 --> 00:16:59.958
Can't. Sorry.

286
00:17:00.542 --> 00:17:01.625
She's ghosting me.

287
00:17:01.708 --> 00:17:03.083
Do you think this is funny?

288
00:17:03.167 --> 00:17:06.792
If she arrests Hayden Payne without proof.
they will sue us into oblivion.

289
00:17:06.875 --> 00:17:10.458
and your daughter will be lucky
to work security at a roadside motel.

290
00:17:10.542 --> 00:17:12.417
Hey! I got proof.

291
00:17:12.500 --> 00:17:13.833
I have a DNA test that proves

292
00:17:13.917 --> 00:17:17.458
the little boy who was murdered
that night was not Matthew Burroughs.

293
00:17:18.042 --> 00:17:19.750
I withdrew that test.

294
00:17:19.833 --> 00:17:21.542
Oh. yeah. Sure you did.

295
00:17:21.625 --> 00:17:23.458
But lucky for Sarah.
there was somebody else

296
00:17:23.542 --> 00:17:26.083
who cared about actually solving the case.

297
00:17:26.167 --> 00:17:30.208
Cheryl Dreason conducted her own DNA test.

298
00:17:31.042 --> 00:17:34.542
The blood at the scene was not a match
for Matthew Burroughs.

299
00:17:34.625 --> 00:17:36.833
That doesn't prove
Hayden Payne kidnapped anyone.

300
00:17:36.917 --> 00:17:38.125
I don't give a shit!

301
00:17:38.208 --> 00:17:40.167
It proves David Burroughs
didn't kill his own son.

302
00:17:40.250 --> 00:17:42.333
And you would've known that
if you weren't so busy

303
00:17:42.417 --> 00:17:44.500
trying to interfere
with Agent Greer's case.

304
00:17:44.583 --> 00:17:46.500
Be a shame if that got out. wouldn't it?

305
00:17:46.583 --> 00:17:47.875
Is that a threat?

306
00:17:47.958 --> 00:17:50.000
Yes! And I got another one for you!

307
00:17:50.625 --> 00:17:54.833
You're gonna send every agent we got
out to the Payne estate right now.

308
00:17:54.917 --> 00:17:57.375
or Dr. Dreason is gonna call…
What's the guy's name?

309
00:17:57.458 --> 00:17:59.625
Jim Doherty. managing editor ofThe Globe.

310
00:17:59.708 --> 00:18:01.708
Jim Doherty. Managing… Did you hear that?

311
00:18:01.792 --> 00:18:03.625
So send them now!

312
00:18:03.708 --> 00:18:04.792
[gunfire]

313
00:18:06.042 --> 00:18:06.958
[Greer] Go.

314
00:18:07.042 --> 00:18:09.542
[suspenseful music playing]

315
00:18:10.458 --> 00:18:11.792
[grunts]

316
00:18:12.375 --> 00:18:13.208
Ah!

317
00:18:14.333 --> 00:18:16.167
[suspenseful music continues]

318
00:18:21.958 --> 00:18:23.583
I brokeyourheart?

319
00:18:24.333 --> 00:18:26.750
You destroyed my family
and then pretended to help us.

320
00:18:26.833 --> 00:18:28.000
Why would you do that?

321
00:18:28.083 --> 00:18:30.458
All I've ever wanted is to be with you.

322
00:18:30.542 --> 00:18:33.958
And then I find out you go to Berg
to start your own family.

323
00:18:34.750 --> 00:18:35.667
Only…

324
00:18:36.917 --> 00:18:38.833
It was supposed to be you.

325
00:18:39.458 --> 00:18:41.292
How did you even find out about that?

326
00:18:41.875 --> 00:18:43.292
[Hayden]My assistant.

327
00:18:43.375 --> 00:18:45.333
She used to be the office manager there.

328
00:18:46.375 --> 00:18:49.875
Before Heller left Berg.
he ensured that I would be the donor.

329
00:18:50.625 --> 00:18:51.667
This is insane.

330
00:18:51.750 --> 00:18:55.125
The whole point of any of this
was for us to have a child.

331
00:18:55.917 --> 00:18:59.125
And when I realized what happened.
that it was Cheryl who went to Berg.

332
00:18:59.208 --> 00:19:00.625
I had to put it out of my mind.

333
00:19:00.708 --> 00:19:05.542
But then you. you brought me to that
Fourth of July party. You remember?

334
00:19:07.542 --> 00:19:09.875
And when I saw him for the first time.

335
00:19:10.958 --> 00:19:12.625
I understood everything.

336
00:19:13.125 --> 00:19:15.958
I knew I was meant to be his father.

337
00:19:16.625 --> 00:19:20.292
And what about the little boy you killed
that night to take Matthew's place?

338
00:19:21.125 --> 00:19:22.042
What about him?

339
00:19:22.125 --> 00:19:25.292
He was gonna die a painful death
from his condition. It doesn't matter.

340
00:19:27.417 --> 00:19:28.708
Can you hear yourself?

341
00:19:31.125 --> 00:19:32.000
Can you?

342
00:19:32.917 --> 00:19:35.083
You're not well. Hayden.

343
00:19:37.250 --> 00:19:39.583
There is something deeply wrong with you.

344
00:19:40.250 --> 00:19:42.125
[Gertrude] Well. now there it is.

345
00:19:43.167 --> 00:19:45.625
Now we know how you really feel about him.

346
00:19:46.208 --> 00:19:49.167
And for the record. I never did like you.

347
00:19:59.625 --> 00:20:01.583
[menacing music playing]

348
00:20:07.833 --> 00:20:08.667
[gunshot]

349
00:20:08.750 --> 00:20:10.042
[body thuds]

350
00:20:16.500 --> 00:20:17.750
[Gertrude] Did you hear that?

351
00:20:18.500 --> 00:20:22.125
Well. it seems as if David Burroughs
has met his unfortunate end.

352
00:20:23.333 --> 00:20:24.708
You won't get away with it.

353
00:20:24.792 --> 00:20:26.500
Don't be so naive.

354
00:20:27.375 --> 00:20:29.250
Hayden. it's time to go.

355
00:20:33.750 --> 00:20:37.500
Everything I've done.
I've done to be with my son.

356
00:20:38.000 --> 00:20:40.125
And I am a good father. Rachel.
He loves me.

357
00:20:43.583 --> 00:20:45.167
He's not your son. Hayden.

358
00:20:46.250 --> 00:20:47.375
Of course he is.

359
00:20:49.667 --> 00:20:51.333
Cheryl was pregnant
before she went to Berg.

360
00:20:51.417 --> 00:20:52.500
Oh. please.

361
00:20:52.583 --> 00:20:54.292
Do a paternity test and you'll see.

362
00:20:54.375 --> 00:20:56.458
We did. And he's a Payne.

363
00:20:56.542 --> 00:20:58.500
Did you see the test. Hayden?

364
00:20:59.958 --> 00:21:02.625
-We don't have time for this. Come on.
-[Rachel] Did you?

365
00:21:02.708 --> 00:21:04.708
[dour music playing]

366
00:21:11.792 --> 00:21:13.042
Is he mine?

367
00:21:14.083 --> 00:21:15.875
Can't you see what she's doing?

368
00:21:16.458 --> 00:21:18.042
He needs to know the truth.

369
00:21:22.292 --> 00:21:25.375
You told me he was my son.

370
00:21:26.708 --> 00:21:27.833
-Enough.
-Answer me.

371
00:21:27.917 --> 00:21:29.583
-[Gertrude] Enough!
-Is he mine?

372
00:21:31.000 --> 00:21:32.958
Don't ask questions…

373
00:21:33.917 --> 00:21:35.875
that you don't want the answers to.

374
00:21:53.792 --> 00:21:55.375
[panting]

375
00:22:01.833 --> 00:22:03.292
[Theo] Who are you?

376
00:22:05.750 --> 00:22:06.958
[David sighing]

377
00:22:07.875 --> 00:22:09.833
[tender music playing]

378
00:22:29.750 --> 00:22:30.792
I'm David.

379
00:22:33.083 --> 00:22:34.250
What's going on?

380
00:22:36.458 --> 00:22:38.083
We're not here to hurt you.

381
00:22:39.458 --> 00:22:40.875
I know you're scared.

382
00:22:41.875 --> 00:22:43.625
I need you to come with us.

383
00:22:44.375 --> 00:22:45.375
[Theo] Why?

384
00:22:52.708 --> 00:22:54.000
You still have Rhino.

385
00:22:55.542 --> 00:22:57.167
How do you know his name?

386
00:22:59.500 --> 00:23:01.292
Because I bought it for you.

387
00:23:02.875 --> 00:23:05.500
You wouldn't remember
because you were three.

388
00:23:13.833 --> 00:23:16.250
Your actual name is Matthew Burroughs.

389
00:23:18.667 --> 00:23:20.083
And I'm your father.

390
00:23:24.583 --> 00:23:26.250
We're gonna take you someplace safe. okay?

391
00:23:26.333 --> 00:23:29.000
I know you're really scared.
but we need to go right now.

392
00:23:32.167 --> 00:23:33.125
Come on.

393
00:23:35.583 --> 00:23:37.958
You said he was my son.

394
00:23:38.042 --> 00:23:39.708
[Gertrude] What did you expect me to do?

395
00:23:40.292 --> 00:23:43.792
There was no going back
after what you did that night.

396
00:23:43.875 --> 00:23:45.875
So I told you what you wanted to hear.

397
00:23:46.458 --> 00:23:49.833
When I got the results.
I made sure you would never find out.

398
00:23:51.125 --> 00:23:54.792
He is the one person who truly loves me!

399
00:23:54.875 --> 00:23:55.792
And he still does.

400
00:23:55.875 --> 00:23:58.667
I'm a good father. and it's the only thing
I've ever been good at!

401
00:23:58.750 --> 00:24:01.250
Hayden. listen to me. Nothing has changed.

402
00:24:01.333 --> 00:24:03.542
Everything has changed!

403
00:24:04.125 --> 00:24:08.167
I have nothing now!
You have taken everything from me!

404
00:24:08.750 --> 00:24:10.458
Oh. that is rich!

405
00:24:10.542 --> 00:24:13.125
I have given you everything!

406
00:24:13.875 --> 00:24:17.208
You were born into status and privilege.

407
00:24:17.292 --> 00:24:18.708
And what did you do with it?

408
00:24:18.792 --> 00:24:23.000
You have brought this family's legacy
to the brink of extinction.

409
00:24:23.083 --> 00:24:26.875
I am not going to allow you
to be a cautionary tale.

410
00:24:27.917 --> 00:24:29.250
You're weak.

411
00:24:30.458 --> 00:24:33.417
Hayden. you've always been weak.

412
00:24:34.000 --> 00:24:35.458
But it's okay.

413
00:24:36.042 --> 00:24:37.583
Because I love you.

414
00:24:38.458 --> 00:24:39.667
And you have me.

415
00:24:41.250 --> 00:24:42.833
You'll always have me.

416
00:24:44.708 --> 00:24:45.833
-[gasps]
-Ah!

417
00:24:47.625 --> 00:24:48.792
[body thuds]

418
00:24:48.875 --> 00:24:51.333
[menacing music playing]

419
00:25:01.875 --> 00:25:03.250
[Greer panting]

420
00:25:03.333 --> 00:25:06.833
Hold on. Hold on. Take him to the car.
I have to go back for Rachel.

421
00:25:06.917 --> 00:25:08.625
You go with her. all right?
You're gonna be safe. I promise.

422
00:25:08.708 --> 00:25:09.750
[gunshot]

423
00:25:12.833 --> 00:25:14.333
You're not taking my son!

424
00:25:14.917 --> 00:25:17.208
Give Theo back. or Rachel dies.

425
00:25:17.292 --> 00:25:19.708
-You don't have to do this. please.
-Lower your weapon.

426
00:25:19.792 --> 00:25:20.750
Not gonna happen.

427
00:25:20.833 --> 00:25:22.500
Put it down now. or she's dead!

428
00:25:22.583 --> 00:25:24.083
Let her go!

429
00:25:24.167 --> 00:25:25.375
Last warning. Hayden!

430
00:25:25.458 --> 00:25:27.458
Give me back my son!

431
00:25:27.542 --> 00:25:29.750
[suspenseful music playing]

432
00:25:30.750 --> 00:25:32.292
-Dad?
-It's okay. buddy.

433
00:25:32.375 --> 00:25:34.292
Don't hurt her. please.

434
00:25:35.792 --> 00:25:36.750
I'll go with you.

435
00:25:36.833 --> 00:25:38.292
No. Matthew.

436
00:25:39.917 --> 00:25:40.833
No!

437
00:25:42.333 --> 00:25:43.417
Don't hurt him. I'm begging you.

438
00:25:43.500 --> 00:25:45.542
-Don't be stupid. Hayden!
-Stop!

439
00:25:46.958 --> 00:25:47.917
Let him go!

440
00:25:48.000 --> 00:25:49.833
[suspenseful music intensifying]

441
00:25:49.917 --> 00:25:51.042
[car door closes]

442
00:25:51.125 --> 00:25:52.750
[tires screeching]

443
00:25:59.208 --> 00:26:00.833
[tires explode. air hisses]

444
00:26:04.250 --> 00:26:06.500
[suspenseful music continues]

445
00:26:12.833 --> 00:26:13.917
Theo!

446
00:26:15.708 --> 00:26:17.333
[panting]

447
00:26:18.292 --> 00:26:20.292
[Theo breathing heavily]

448
00:26:28.333 --> 00:26:29.667
Theo?

449
00:26:31.833 --> 00:26:33.292
Where are you. buddy?

450
00:26:33.375 --> 00:26:35.333
[muted tense music playing]

451
00:26:37.917 --> 00:26:41.083
Those people. they--
They want to take you away!

452
00:26:43.542 --> 00:26:46.792
Whatever they told you. it isn't true!

453
00:26:46.875 --> 00:26:48.542
We're family. you and me!

454
00:26:49.125 --> 00:26:51.000
I love you. You know that!

455
00:26:51.750 --> 00:26:52.875
Oh!

456
00:26:54.125 --> 00:26:55.667
[both grunting]

457
00:27:01.792 --> 00:27:03.750
[intense music playing]

458
00:27:05.583 --> 00:27:06.958
[grunts]

459
00:27:10.958 --> 00:27:11.792
[Rachel] David!

460
00:27:12.583 --> 00:27:14.292
Drop the gun. Drop it now!

461
00:27:18.333 --> 00:27:19.708
[panting]

462
00:27:21.500 --> 00:27:24.000
All I ever wanted was a family of my own.

463
00:27:24.833 --> 00:27:26.583
You can still do the right thing.

464
00:27:27.458 --> 00:27:28.375
Just let him go.

465
00:27:28.458 --> 00:27:30.208
[dramatic music playing]

466
00:27:36.167 --> 00:27:38.500
You're the best thing
that ever happened to me.

467
00:27:43.583 --> 00:27:45.333
[dramatic music swelling]

468
00:27:46.667 --> 00:27:47.708
No!

469
00:27:49.500 --> 00:27:50.958
[gasps softly]

470
00:27:52.083 --> 00:27:52.917
David.

471
00:27:57.000 --> 00:28:00.375
I'm right here. Stay with me. come on.
Come on. I'm right here.

472
00:28:01.375 --> 00:28:03.125
[calming music playing]

473
00:28:06.167 --> 00:28:07.542
I found you.

474
00:28:09.500 --> 00:28:11.042
[distant police sirens]

475
00:28:11.125 --> 00:28:12.917
[Rachel] I'm right here. all right?

476
00:28:13.000 --> 00:28:14.792
Stay with me. Come on.

477
00:28:14.875 --> 00:28:16.042
David.

478
00:28:16.125 --> 00:28:17.917
[police sirens fading]

479
00:28:25.958 --> 00:28:27.792
[indistinct chatter]

480
00:28:29.792 --> 00:28:31.792
[David]My name is David Burroughs.

481
00:28:31.875 --> 00:28:35.542
I served five years of a life sentence
for killing my son.

482
00:28:35.625 --> 00:28:38.167
Until I broke out of prison to rescue him.

483
00:28:38.750 --> 00:28:41.125
If you're from Boston.
you might've read about it.

484
00:28:42.292 --> 00:28:43.958
If you're not. you will soon.

485
00:28:44.750 --> 00:28:46.167
Within weeks of saving Matthew.

486
00:28:46.250 --> 00:28:48.708
my conviction was overturned
and I was freed.

487
00:28:48.792 --> 00:28:52.000
But I wasn't the only one who was given
the blessing of a new beginning.

488
00:28:52.083 --> 00:28:54.542
Cheryl gave birth to a baby girl.

489
00:28:55.500 --> 00:28:57.833
And after what Ronald did
to help us find Matthew.

490
00:28:57.917 --> 00:29:00.125
he and Cheryl found their way
back to each other.

491
00:29:01.042 --> 00:29:03.333
But not all new beginnings are planned.

492
00:29:03.417 --> 00:29:06.583
Some are born of necessity
and even consequence.

493
00:29:06.667 --> 00:29:08.917
Adam lost his shield
for helping me escape.

494
00:29:09.000 --> 00:29:12.000
The upside was Nicky
had no use for him as a civilian.

495
00:29:12.083 --> 00:29:15.042
He works as a PI now
with another former cop from the BPD.

496
00:29:15.125 --> 00:29:17.583
Did you invoice the wife
on that babysitter case?

497
00:29:17.667 --> 00:29:20.458
Yeah. I will.
As soon as you stop busting my balls.

498
00:29:20.542 --> 00:29:21.500
What balls?

499
00:29:21.583 --> 00:29:24.750
[David]I'm not sure if we'll ever
be the brothers we once were.

500
00:29:24.833 --> 00:29:27.792
But I do know without his help.
I wouldn't be here.

501
00:29:28.583 --> 00:29:31.792
I wouldn't be here
without the help of a lot of people.

502
00:29:32.583 --> 00:29:34.292
Agent Greer took over for her dad

503
00:29:34.375 --> 00:29:37.750
as head of the Boston Fugitive Task Force
when Max retired.

504
00:29:37.833 --> 00:29:39.292
[knock on door]

505
00:29:39.375 --> 00:29:40.708
Or at least tried to retire.

506
00:29:40.792 --> 00:29:43.083
-What are you doing here?
-[Williams] I just came by.

507
00:29:43.167 --> 00:29:45.042
Thought maybe you might
want to go to lunch.

508
00:29:45.125 --> 00:29:49.250
Well. I'm sorry.
I'm actually really swamped in a case.

509
00:29:49.333 --> 00:29:51.000
Oh. well. is. um…

510
00:29:51.917 --> 00:29:53.833
What. you got something that. uh…

511
00:29:54.875 --> 00:29:57.125
maybe you need another set of eyes on?

512
00:29:58.292 --> 00:30:00.750
[heartfelt music playing]

513
00:30:08.917 --> 00:30:11.417
[David]My father passed away
less than a week ago.

514
00:30:11.500 --> 00:30:14.083
But not before getting to spend
several months with his grandson.

515
00:30:14.750 --> 00:30:18.833
instilling as much information about
the Boston Red Sox as humanly possible.

516
00:30:18.917 --> 00:30:20.583
[gentle music playing]

517
00:30:30.375 --> 00:30:31.458
-[door closes]
-Sorry.

518
00:30:31.542 --> 00:30:33.333
I'll go back inside soon.

519
00:30:35.250 --> 00:30:36.375
It's okay.

520
00:30:42.708 --> 00:30:45.458
Sometimes with a lot of people.
I just get…

521
00:30:46.542 --> 00:30:47.667
I don't know.

522
00:30:49.250 --> 00:30:50.417
Yeah. me too.

523
00:30:51.833 --> 00:30:53.500
Before Lenny died.

524
00:30:53.583 --> 00:30:57.750
he told me a story about a barbecue
I was at on the Fourth of July.

525
00:30:58.792 --> 00:31:00.208
Yeah. that was his favorite holiday.

526
00:31:01.125 --> 00:31:03.708
I told him I remembered
because he was sick.

527
00:31:05.000 --> 00:31:06.042
But I didn't.

528
00:31:07.583 --> 00:31:08.708
I want to.

529
00:31:10.667 --> 00:31:12.250
What if I never do?

530
00:31:13.375 --> 00:31:16.042
Great thing about memories
is you can make more of them.

531
00:31:18.083 --> 00:31:20.708
It's just people don't appreciate
how special they are.

532
00:31:24.292 --> 00:31:25.458
But you will.

533
00:31:27.958 --> 00:31:29.000
Yeah.

534
00:31:29.667 --> 00:31:31.583
["Hero" by Family of the Year playing]

535
00:31:31.667 --> 00:31:35.333
[David]What Matthew's been through.
few people can understand.

536
00:31:35.417 --> 00:31:37.458
Luckily. I'm one of them.

537
00:31:37.542 --> 00:31:40.458
Our shared struggle back to the life
we were supposed to have

538
00:31:40.542 --> 00:31:43.625
has bonded us in both heartbreak and hope.

539
00:31:43.708 --> 00:31:46.000
-There he is.
-Hello.

540
00:31:46.083 --> 00:31:48.250
♪ Let me go ♪

541
